  "riddle": "1. Begin your journey at a renowned lodging space in Portland, iconic for its history. In what year did this elegant structure first welcome guests?\n\n2. If the year you unearthed was a day of the week like no other, which one would it be on the first of January? Represent it numerically, with Monday as one and Sunday as seven.\n\n3. Track down the towering figure who led a legendary NBA team, famed for his strategic mind. What is his measured height, expressed in feet and inches?\n\n4. Within the pages of basketball history, discover the gentleman drafted in 1958—what position did he hold in that monumental selection?\n\n5. Seek the next prime number that springs to mind after that significant round count found previously. \n\n6. A celebrated coach stood tall in the world of collegiate basketball—how high was this mentor, measured in feet?\n\n7. A renowned coaching career blossomed in Kentucky across multiple memorable seasons. How many years did this coach rally his team to glory?\n\n8. Next, focus on an historic mansion that whispers tales of the past. What is the elevation in feet above sea level at the address where it resides?\n\n9. Uncover the achievements of a female basketball player who made waves in college. What institution did she represent, and during which years did she play?\n\n10. If you hit the road from an iconic spot in New Mexico to the heart of Portland, how many minutes would your journey take?\n\n11. A curious transformation awaits! What figure do you get when you flip the digits of the travel duration number extracted earlier? \n\n12. In the realm of sports accolades, how many different athletic disciplines receive recognition through the esteemed award you seek?\n\n13. Venture to discover the moment this influential sports channel made its grand debut. When did it first go live?\n\n14. Nearby the broadcasting hub, how many places of worship stand tall and proud? Count them carefully.\n\n15. In the dynamic world of music culture, find out how many different language links grace the top of an article about a vibrant new genre. \n\n16. Onward to the air force lore, convert six kilometers into miles — what figure do you arrive at?\n\n17. After exploring the narratives and numbers, compute the absolute difference between clue 4 and clue 6, reduced modulo 10. Your answer will reveal a single digit, leading you to the treasure.",
